Jenkins + Git + Maven Setup (Amazon Linux) – Step by Step

## Step 1: Change the Hostname

Check the current hostname.
```bash
cat /etc/hostname
```
Edit the hostname file.
```bash
sudo vi /etc/hostname
```
Example:   jenkins_server

Change the hostname immediately.
```bash
sudo hostnamectl set-hostname jenkins_server
```
Verify:

hostname
Step 2: Install Java (Required for Jenkins)

Update the server.

sudo yum update -y

Install Java 17.

sudo yum install java-17-amazon-corretto-devel -y

Verify Java.

java -version
Step 3: Install Git

Install Git.

sudo yum install git -y

Verify installation.

git --version

Find the Git binary path.

which git

Example output:

/usr/bin/git

Save this path. It will be used in Jenkins.

